version: 1
display_name: VCFE-9X-000042 - The ESX host must enforce a 90-day maximum password lifetime restriction.
global_description: |-
  Any password, no matter how complex, can eventually be cracked. Therefore, passwords need to be changed periodically. If the VMM does not limit the lifetime of passwords and force users to change their passwords, there is the risk that the VMM passwords could be compromised.
osfinger: []  # API/proxy-managed control; not tied to a minion OS grain
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFE-9X-000042
  srg:
    - SRG-OS-000076-VMM-000430
  cci:
    - CCI-004066
  nist:
    - IA-5 (1) (h)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_vsphere_esx:
    type: custom
    desc: The ESX host must enforce a 90-day maximum password lifetime restriction.
    control_id: VCFE-9X-000042
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      From the vSphere Client, go to Hosts and Clusters.

      Select the ESX Host >> Configure >> System >> Advanced System Settings.

      Select the "Security.PasswordMaxDays" value and verify it is set to "90".

      or

      From a PowerCLI command prompt while connected to the ESX host, run the following command:

      Get-VMHost | Get-AdvancedSetting -Name Security.PasswordMaxDays

      If the "Security.PasswordMaxDays" setting is not set to "90", this is a finding.
    rationale: |-
      Any password, no matter how complex, can eventually be cracked. Therefore, passwords need to be changed periodically. If the VMM does not limit the lifetime of passwords and force users to change their passwords, there is the risk that the VMM passwords could be compromised.
    remediation: |-
      From the vSphere Client, go to Hosts and Clusters.

      Select the ESX Host >> Configure >> System >> Advanced System Settings.

      Click "Edit". Select the "Security.PasswordMaxDays" value and configure it to "90".

      or

      From a PowerCLI command prompt while connected to the ESX host, run the following command:

      Get-VMHost | Get-AdvancedSetting -Name Security.PasswordMaxDays | Set-AdvancedSetting -Value 90
